urlLink INFORMATION SKILLS VIA THE WEB: REPORT OF A PROJECT IN PROGRESS  A This paper is by Barbara White and Ruth Quinn of Northern Territory University. It was presented at the Lifelong learning conference, Central Queensland University, 2000.   Abstract:   This paper will discuss the Information Skills program at the Northern Territory University Library, which has developed from limited, voluntary face-to-face sessions, to the inclusion of information skills into the curriculum for the Common Units, and the development of web-based modules. Challenges experienced along the way will be discussed.